  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Flood Response in Odisha</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Material Support for Home Restoration: This activity will protect families from the coming winter season, while ensuring their privacy and safety. Identified households will be supported with shelter kits&#x2014;which will include bamboo poles, roofing supplies, ropes, and other materials needed to repair shelters.
2. Cash-for-Work for Agriculture and Shelter Recovery: The project will initiate Cash-for-Work (CfW) programming for households whose agricultural land has been heavily silted to return their lands to a subsistence level of productivity. Both men and women will be encouraged to participate in CfW activities. With limited or no options to restore livelihoods of the affected communities, CfW activities will support income generation and restoration of infrastructure, such as village roads.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mercy Corps will immediately begin implementing programs in the Badasahi subdivision in the Mayurbhanj District. Our areas of focus will be on shelter restoration (benefiting 180 households, 1,080 individuals), and agriculture
recovery (benefiting 200 households and 1,200 individuals).</narrative>
  </description>
